). The fact\nthat VCC848 is still (atomic) gas-dominated after the period of most violent\ncollision suggests that gas-rich dwarf galaxy merging can result in BCD-like\nremnants with extended atomic gas distribution surrounding a blue compact\ncenter, in general agreement with previous numerical simulations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Feb 2020 19:23:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-11"}
